You are given an integer array nums and an integer k.

The task is to determine whether there are two identical numbers in the array such that:

The distance between their indices is at most k

📍 Example 1
nums = [1, 2, 3, 1], k = 3

Let’s check occurrences of 1:

First 1 at index 0
Second 1 at index 3

Distance = 3 - 0 = 3 → which is ≤ k

✔ So answer is true

📍 Example 2
nums = [1, 0, 1, 1], k = 1

Occurrences of 1:

index 0 and 2 → distance = 2 ❌ (too far)
index 2 and 3 → distance = 1 ✔ (valid)

✔ So answer is true

Solution:
fun main() {
 val nums = intArrayOf(1, 2, 3, 1)
 val k = 3
    
 val set = mutableSetOf<Int>()
    
    for(i in nums.indices){
        if(set.contains(nums[i])){
            println(true)
            break
        }
        set.add(nums[i])
        
        if(set.size > k){
            set.remove(nums[i - k])
        }
    }

}
